<title>JAPAN: Many Japan firms rally on stock buy-back plan.</title>
<headline>Many Japan firms rally on stock buy-back plan.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in companies that announced on Monday that they would buy back their own stocks rallied in morning trade on Tuesday, traders said.</p>
<p>At 0200 GMT, shares in Nichimen Corp were 27 yen higher at 411, after having been bid-only. Shares in Mars Engineering Co Ltd were bid-only at 2,360 yen, against Monday's close of 2,200.</p>
<p>On the Osaka Securities Exchange (OSE), Benesse Corp jumped 550 yen to 6,880 yen, while Autobacs Seven Co Ltd rose 180 yen to 8,510, after having been bid-only.  </p>
<p>Shares in Autobacs briefly surged as high as 8,900 yen overnight in London.</p>
<p>&quot;These companies announced share buy-back plans and they attracted buying,&quot; said a trader with a second-tier Japanese securities house.</p>
